<h2>What about video AI tools?</h2>

<p>Indian creators ask about Runway, Pika, Synthesia, HeyGen often. Honest answer for 2026: video AI tools are powerful but expensive in INR (&#8377;2,500 to &#8377;15,000/month) and the output still feels uncanny for face-to-camera work. Use them for B-roll, transitions, or background loops, not for replacing your on-camera work. Wait 6 to 12 months before subscribing if you are budget conscious.</p>

<h2>How to pay for AI tools as an Indian creator</h2>

<p>If you have a Razorpay or sponsorship-funded business account, that goes through smoothly. For personal subscriptions, use a forex card or Niyo Global, regular Indian cards get rejected often. Canva is the easy one, Indian billing in INR. Read the full payment guide: <a href="/guides/pay-for-ai-tools-india/">5 ways to pay for AI tools from India</a>.</p>

<h2>Tax notes for Indian creators</h2>

<p>If you earn from YouTube AdSense, brand sponsorships, or affiliate income, the AI tool subscription is a fully deductible business expense. Keep the GST invoice (most providers issue one in your billing dashboard) and claim input tax credit if you are GST-registered.</p>

